In England, in the seven days to 09 June, there were 58,590 new confirmed cases (103.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 June, there were 35,620 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 64% (22,970 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 June is 18,870,862 (33,370.1 cases per 100,000 population).
